grocery shopping tips for a family always on the go hubby and i work different shifts and boys are in middleschool and highschool and i need to cut back on the fast food want to start having more healthy snacks and meals mt best recommendation is to get organize with a recipe software program that simplifies everything once initially set up most software programs besides having thousands of recipes in them also have the ability to add your own but the real benefits for you would be the menu and meal planning menu's once you have that you can create shopping lists for the week based upon the menu plan you created some programs also offer the pantry inventory feature where you can enter what you already have in your pantry and it eliminates it from you grocery list and you can also find recipes based upon what you already have other perks are most have nutritional breakdowns off all the recipes serving conversion calculator and the ability to import export recipes i love mine and it makes everything regarding feeding the family so much easier the link below is the one i use they run about and in most cases you can download the software hope this helps and good luck Recipe Food ITunes WordPerfect Nutrition Wal-Mart Diablo II: Lord of Destruction Numerical analysis System 7 (Macintosh) Ramen OpenOffice.org Windows XP Embedded system SAS System French fries Dietitian Veganism Japanese cuisine Windows Vista XML Tea MSN Messenger ZX Spectrum PlayStation Portable Bread Object Desktop Expert system Super Size Me Mach kernel Breakfast Screenshot Mozilla Firefox Saimin Restaurant Recursion Dieting Ketchup Stomach cancer Snack food Software engineering Omega-3 fatty acid Cheese Atari 8-bit family RISC Raw food diet Delicatessen Cuisine of Denmark X Window System Mac OS X v10.4 Pok__mon Ruby and Sapphire AmigaOS Pretty Good Privacy Visual Basic Copy protection Hypoglycemia In-N-Out Burger Breastfeeding Linux Trans fat Microeconomics Emacs History of the graphical user interface 